---
// DirectionsFigure — the two directions of inference.
// Top: productivity (structure → many conclusions, cheap).
// Bottom: minimum licensing structure (behavior → smallest structure, expensive, accent).
---
<figure class="essay-fig">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 640 244" role="img" aria-label="Productivity fans conclusions out cheaply; minimum licensing structure is the expensive reverse direction">
    <defs>
      <marker id="df-arrow" viewBox="0 0 10 10" refX="9" refY="5" markerWidth="6" markerHeight="6" orient="auto-start-reverse">
        <path d="M 0 0 L 10 5 L 0 10 z" fill="currentColor" />
      </marker>
    </defs>

    <!-- Row 1: productivity (cheap) -->
    <text class="row-lbl" x="20" y="20">productivity · structure → conclusions · cheap</text>
    <circle class="node" cx="78" cy="62" r="15" />
    <text class="node-tag" x="78" y="94" text-anchor="middle">structure</text>
    <line class="arrow" x1="94" y1="62" x2="552" y2="24" marker-end="url(#df-arrow)" />
    <line class="arrow" x1="94" y1="62" x2="552" y2="48" marker-end="url(#df-arrow)" />
    <line class="arrow" x1="94" y1="62" x2="552" y2="72" marker-end="url(#df-arrow)" />
    <line class="arrow" x1="94" y1="62" x2="552" y2="96" marker-end="url(#df-arrow)" />
    <circle class="dot" cx="562" cy="24" r="4.5" />
    <circle class="dot" cx="562" cy="48" r="4.5" />
    <circle class="dot" cx="562" cy="72" r="4.5" />
    <circle class="dot" cx="562" cy="96" r="4.5" />

    <line class="mid" x1="20" y1="120" x2="620" y2="120" />

    <!-- Row 2: minimum licensing structure (expensive, accent) -->
    <text class="row-lbl row-lbl-accent" x="20" y="144">minimum licensing · behavior → smallest structure · expensive</text>
    <circle class="dot" cx="562" cy="158" r="4.5" />
    <circle class="dot" cx="562" cy="182" r="4.5" />
    <circle class="dot" cx="562" cy="206" r="4.5" />
    <circle class="dot" cx="562" cy="230" r="4.5" />
    <line class="arrow arrow-accent" x1="552" y1="158" x2="96" y2="194" marker-end="url(#df-arrow)" />
    <line class="arrow arrow-accent" x1="552" y1="182" x2="96" y2="194" marker-end="url(#df-arrow)" />
    <line class="arrow arrow-accent" x1="552" y1="206" x2="96" y2="194" marker-end="url(#df-arrow)" />
    <line class="arrow arrow-accent" x1="552" y1="230" x2="96" y2="194" marker-end="url(#df-arrow)" />
    <circle class="node node-accent" cx="78" cy="194" r="14" />
    <text class="node-tag node-tag-accent" x="78" y="226" text-anchor="middle">smallest</text>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>
    Generating conclusions is cheap — anything that composes fans out for free. The reverse
    direction (accent) is the expensive one: given a behavior, the smallest causal structure that
    <em>must</em> be there for it to land.
  </figcaption>
</figure>

<style>
  .essay-fig svg { color: var(--color-text-muted); max-height: 250px; }
  .node { fill: var(--color-bg); stroke: var(--color-text-muted); stroke-width: 1.25; }
  .node-accent { stroke: var(--color-accent); stroke-width: 1.5; }
  .dot { fill: var(--color-text-dim); }
  .arrow { stroke: var(--color-text-dim); color: var(--color-text-dim); stroke-width: 1; fill: none; }
  .arrow-accent { stroke: var(--color-accent); color: var(--color-accent); stroke-width: 1.25; }
  .mid { stroke: var(--color-border); stroke-width: 0.5; stroke-dasharray: 2 3; }
  .row-lbl { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; fill: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .row-lbl-accent { fill: var(--color-accent); }
  .node-tag { font-family: var(--font-sans); font-size: 10px; fill: var(--color-text-muted); }
  .node-tag-accent { fill: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
